ðŸ›¼ Meet Nadine
Nadine has been dancing non-stop since she was four, from ballet, jazz, and contemporary to hip hop, waacking, dancehall, and heels. Her journey eventually led her to roller dancing, where she discovered that all the styles she had explored could beautifully blend on wheels.

Realizing there were very few roller skate instructors in developing countries, she took the initiative to learn from international skaters â€” joining courses and workshops abroad to build her skills.

She co-founded @oneskateasia to help grow the roller dance scene locally, dedicating herself to spreading the joy of skating and creating more space for others to roll into their rhythm.

A forever student at heart, Nadine stays curious, always learning, evolving, and sharing the journey with others.
